      <div class="te-block">
        <p>Pseudomyxoma Peritonei (PMP) peritoneal surface oncology లో unique disease. Appendix లో low-grade mucinous tumour peritoneal cavity లోకి spread అయి, mucin (jelly-like material) accumulate అవుతుంది. Slowly progressive, decades లో.</p>
        <p>PMP కి CRS+HIPEC best treatment. Sugarbaker technique development తరువాత, ఈ disease "incurable" నుండి "potentially curable" గా shift అయింది. నా Hannover fellowship లో PMP specific cases extensively cover అయ్యాయి.</p>
        <p>PMP diagnosed patients కి నేను ఒక honest thing చెప్తాను. ఈ disease కి specialist who knows peritoneal surface oncology specifically అవసరం. General surgeon కి Whipple's పెద్దది అనిపించవచ్చు. కానీ PMP కి, CRS+HIPEC experience ఉన్న surgeon definitely seek చేయాలి.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="en-block">
        <p>Pseudomyxoma Peritonei (PMP) is a unique disease in peritoneal surface oncology. A low-grade mucinous tumour in the appendix spreads into the peritoneal cavity and accumulates mucin (a jelly-like material). It is slowly progressive, over decades.</p>
        <p>CRS+HIPEC is the best treatment for PMP. Following the development of the Sugarbaker technique, this disease shifted from "incurable" to "potentially curable". My Hannover fellowship covered PMP cases extensively.</p>
        <p>I tell PMP patients one honest thing. This disease needs a specialist who knows peritoneal surface oncology specifically. A general surgeon might find a Whipple's challenging. But for PMP, you should definitely seek a surgeon with CRS+HIPEC experience.</p>
      </div>
